Frame-dragging removes the usual distinction between accelerated frames (which show gravitational effects) and inertial frames (where the geometry is supposedly free from gravitational fields). Park made two $1000 donations to [[John Kerry]]{{'}}s Presidential Campaign. Park reportedly said it was "pure happenstance" that Kerry wrote a letter recommending Park for a position at the Federal Home Loan Bank of New York one month after the two donations were made. FEC records do not show any donations to federal candidates besides [[John Kerry]] during this period.<ref name=":1" />
